## Checklist
- [ ] Assets enumerated before threats; each asset has at least one
      actor associated with it.
- [ ] STRIDE walk performed per (asset, actor) pair; pairs with no
      plausible threat are explicitly dropped, not silently ignored.
- [ ] Every threat cites a mitigation: existing file:line, proposed
      change, or accepted residual with owner signature.
- [ ] Ownership map identifies which skill or review surface catches
      regressions for each mitigation.
- [ ] Trust boundaries on the change are named and the actor that
      crosses each one is listed.

## Asset table
Use this table as the primary artifact; threats row-reference it.

| asset | data class | actors | trust_boundary | owner |
|-------|------------|--------|----------------|-------|
| "<name>" | public / internal / confidential / regulated | ["<actor>"] | "<where it crosses a boundary>" | "<service or team>" |

Threats then attach to asset rows:

| asset | actor | stride | mitigation | residual | owner |
|-------|-------|--------|------------|----------|-------|
| "<asset>" | "<actor>" | S/T/R/I/D/E | "<file:line or proposed>" | none / accepted-by:<name> | "<skill or review surface>" |
